Spec: Logger Service
Purpose:
  Provide shared CLI notice logging with level-specific colored output.

Structure:
  ./logger.ts: Logger service implementation.
  ./logger.test.ts: Logger service tests.

Owns:
  ./logger.ts
  ./logger.test.ts

References:
  ../config/config.sdd

Must:
  Expose a simple method-based API for log levels.
  Support error, warn, log, info, and debug notice levels.
  Color each notice level consistently with chalk.
  Write error notices to stderr.
  Write non-error notices to stdout.
  Accept @Config through constructor parameters.
  Read log_level from @Config.
  Treat log_level as the minimum notice level to write.
  Support error, warning, warn, log, info, and debug log_level values.
  Validate log_level before writing notices.
  Allow output streams to be injected for tests.
  Treat ordinary notice writes as best-effort and not throw for normal logger use.

Depends on:
  @CliError
  @Config
  chalk
  Node.js stdout and stderr streams

Exposes:
  @Logger
  @Logger.error
  @Logger.warn
  @Logger.log
  @Logger.info
  @Logger.debug

Accepts:
  @LoggerOptions
  string notice message

Returns:
  void

Raises:
  @InvalidLogLevelError
